modules.description: Implements a single-file filesystem storing arbitrary data in a block device. Provides atomic read, write, and reset operations with checksum validation. Useful for small persistent state storage like configuration files or metadata in disk images.

Implements a single-file filesystem for storing arbitrary data in a block device. Provides atomic read, write, and reset operations with checksum validation. Suitable for managing small persistent state such as configuration files or metadata within disk images.
